posts.title: Check Out This Aussie Overwatch Trash Talking Comedy Series
posts.text:
Jake Barros December 7, 2017 
SODIUM SQUAD is a new comedy web series from Brisbane based production company Stranger Films, following a trash-tier team of Overwatch players. Led by Reynolds, their ambitious and scheming captain, the dysfunctional team try to skill up and climb the season rankings. 
Joined by a basement-dwelling edgelord, an excitable Twitch streamer, a house-bound gym junkie and an anonymous fifth member that takes role playing a little too seriously, they try every outlandish strategy in the playbook to try to win – but their efforts are perpetually undermined by silly infighting, personality clashes, burnt pizza pockets and terrible internet 
After the successful release of their pilot episode ‘Placements’ – they’re now crowdfunding for their first season. If it reaches its goal on Kickstarter they’ll begin production in early 2018. 
I watched episode 1 here at the Press Start HQ and this is definitely a series we’ll be keeping our eyes on. In the last few days, it’s received great praise on YouTube and Reddit with 100’s of comments coming through from Overwatch fans and players supporting the series and wanting to see more! 
If you’ve ever played a FPS and thought “I’ve got what it takes to go competitive” to then realise “My K/D’s 0.2…it’s still good” this is definitely worth the watch. 
You can watch the pilot episode below, as well as checking out their Kickstarter and Facebook page . Jake Barros Press Start Video Creator and Co-Host of The Start Cast. Making videos and playing video games is totally my thing. It's all about the story and entertainment value for me in both of these. I love a good FPS, RPG or action/adventure! thread.title: Smallest eigenvalue of the sum of positive semidefinite non-commuting Hermitian matrices
thread.title_full: Smallest eigenvalue of the sum of positive semidefinite non-commuting Hermitian matrices

posts.author: AG1123
posts.title: Smallest eigenvalue of the sum of positive semidefinite non-commuting Hermitian matrices
posts.text:
up vote 1 down vote favorite 
Let $A$ and $B$ be $n \times n$ Hermitian matrices with distinct eigenvalues $a_n>\ldots>a_1$ and $b_n>\ldots>b_1$ respectively. From Weyl's inequalities it follows that the smallest eigenvalue $s_1$ of their sum, $S=A+B$, must obey $$ s_1\geq a_1 + b_1 \,. $$ Assume, in addition, that $A$ and $B$ are positive semidefinite and that they don't commute, i.e. $[A,B]=AB-BA\neq 0$. Is it true in this case that last inequality becomes a strict inequality, that is $s_1 > a_1 + b_1$? If so, how can one prove this and if not could you provide an argument or counter-example? Also, if not, what extra restrictions should $A$ and $B$ obey so that the strict inequality holds? 
Thanks!

thread.title_full: Fifth national population and housing census scheduled for April 2019

posts.author: vivian
posts.title: Fifth national population and housing census scheduled for April 2019
posts.text:
Fifth national population and housing census scheduled for April 2019 Fifth national population and housing census scheduled for April 2019   Prime Minister has issued Directive 44/CT-TTg on the organisation of the fifth national population and housing census in April, 2019. A census taker collects information at a family 
The census, to be launched at 0:00 hour on April 1, 2019, is conducted to assess the implementation of socio-economic development policies and plans in 2011-2020 and serve as reference for the building of socio-economic development policies and plans for 2021-2030. 
The directive assigns specific tasks for ministries, ministerial-level agencies,   and People’s Committees of provinces   to prepare for the census. 
The General Statistics Office (GSO), under the instruction of the Ministry of Planning and Investment, is to coordinate with ministries, ministerial-level agencies,   and People’s Committees of provinces   to build plans on conducting the census, carrying out piloting surveys and rehearsal. All preparations and rehearsals must be completed in the fourth quarter of 2018. 
The Finance Ministry, in collaboration with the Finance Ministry, is tasked with preparing the census cost estimate and setting aside budget for the census. 
The Ministry of Information and Communication must build communication plans to popularise the census. 
Ministries, ministerial-level agencies,   and People’s Committees of provinces   have the responsibility to provide administrative data for the census.- VNA

Spaceplanes are cool and open up new possibilities but I really want the next version of KSP (if there is one) to have a fully featured autopilot*, like MechJeb but more reliable. One that can control rockets and spaceplanes, and can handle landing on planets with atmosphere as well. I enjoy building stuff and orbital maneuvers but take offs and landings are a chore that I never really enjoyed. MJ works fine on air-less planets but I was never able to land reliably on Duna. Maybe I'm just too stupid to play KSP.
Said autopilot would also perform maneuvers in the background so I can focus on something else while my n+1 supply vessel is getting to orbit.
*before any reality fan freaks out, this would have the option to be disabled in difficulty settings.

posts.text:
By Charles Lewis 

A good voice tutor will always be very hard to find. You have to be very keen when you are looking for one as they will make you develop your career. Use the guidelines below to find the best voice lessons Warren County institution.

One that is located near your home or place of work will have an added advantage. This is because you will spend less time to get to the classes. You will also not miss classes because you are near them instead of being held by traffic. One that is far will be too expensive because you will always have to pay for transportation. Let the internet help you to get one located near the place you are.

You do not have to spend beyond your budget. This can be achieved after you get to know the fees you have to pay. Start by contacting different schools to get to know the charges for all the sessions. You will then have to compare the rates before you resort to one that is economical to you. Also get to ensure they have quality tutors for you to feel the value of the money you are giving out.

Ask the administration to give you the qualifications of the tutors. You can be able to find out if they have been trained to teach you. They should have at least a degree for you to be certain they have been trained. Look at their experience to determine if they have different skills that they use to approach to students. Their experience performance should be very high for you to be absolute of obtaining the best.

Let the internet help you to know if the teachers from the school have been registered to teach you. Some of them may have fake qualifications and have not been approved to teach. These unions will have a full list of all the members, and you have to go through them. Confirm if their names appear on the list to be satisfied. Do not get the services of a teacher who is not on the list as some of them may not be qualified.

Interact with the teachers to find out whether or not they are friendly. You need an expert who is friendly to ensure you are comfortable and acquire maximum assistance. They will specifically teach one to develop a wonderful voice. You should tell them what you need to obtain from all the lessons and see if they will agree with you. They are the ones who will help you achieve what you are looking for.

Ask the facility or the tutor to provide you with a list of referrals who you will contact. These are the ones who will give you a testimonial about what they obtained. Ask them if they were satisfied with the mode of teaching and if they can recommend you to the school.

Consult the tutor and ask them if they can teach you according to the style you want. This is because you might want to be taught how to have this classical voice. One that will agree to teach you should be chosen because they will dedicate themselves to it.

You can find a list of the advantages you get when you take voice lessons Warren County area at http://www.yellowhousemusicstudio.com right now.

thread.section_title: Meetings With Death: Chapter 21 – Mulberry Words
thread.title: Meetings With Death: Chapter 21
thread.title_full: Meetings With Death: Chapter 21

posts.author: mulberrywords
posts.title: Meetings With Death: Chapter 21
posts.text:
He moved away from the sidelines and towards me with a determination that left me breathless. I had to look away from the deep sadness in my grandmother’s eyes. Had Mandla succeeded? Would I ever see my mother or Mvikeli ever again? There was so much that I wanted to have achieved. My anger spiked at the injustice of it all. I vowed to spend the rest of my life haunting Mandla. I was dying and Death was coming for me. He stood in front of me drinking me in with his bejewelled eyes as he reached out to me. He felt sad, and that realisation punched a hole in the bubble of my anger until I was thoroughly deflated. I threw myself into his arms, both seeking and offering comfort.
He took me back to my mother and Mvikeli. The scene that met us stabbed through my heart. My body was lying on the ground next to the rock formation and Mvikeli was lying on the ground where I had left him standing. The shamans were kneeling down, fighting to keep my soul tethered to my body while Eana stood over Mvikeli, calling him back. I screamed.
Mvikeli could not be dead. The complete stillness of his body pierced my soul. How could he cease to exist? I ran closer to his body and that’s where I saw his soul, hovering just above his body and not yet fully disconnected. He wasn’t dead. The relief washed over me, a balm like no other to soothe the acute hurt that had torn through me. Eana was frantic in her efforts but I could see that she was not winning. It was only a matter of time before he was well and truly dead. She called out for help but the only people around to help were trying to keep me tethered to my body. I turned to him, keenly aware of my trembling weakness exposed to him in its entirety.
“Please, don’t take him. Not yet. Please.”
“I do not have a say in whether or not he lives.”
“You brought me back!”
Anger flared behind his hard gaze.
“That was a different case.”
I wanted to argue some more but Mvikeli did not have the time for us to be at each other’s throats right now. I turned to my mother, willing her with the dwindling power I had to let me go and save Mvikeli.
“If they let go you will die. You would sacrifice your life for his?”
“I could not live with the grief of his loss.”
Nothing about my wish right now was born from a selfless intent. I was not a hero, I was a girl who could not face the loss of a man she now knew she loved. My mother looked up, tears streaming down her face as she understood my wishes. My shoulders sagged as she finally got up and rushed towards Mvikeli’s prone body. Buhle joined her as they systematically looked for Mvikeli’s bane. He knelt beside me and gathered me into his arms. For a second I allowed the pleasure of his proximity to lull me out of the sheer panic I had been immersed in not moments ago. But then as the real world faded away into nothingness I remembered that I was dead.
We alighted in a valley carpeted with lush green grass. The trees were laden with yellow fruits that looked like mangoes. The sound of a river nearby as it trickled passed was melodious and in perfect harmonies with the birds tweeting in the tees. Something was off though, the grass seemed too green, the mangoes too yellow and the birds never missed a note. The sky was too blue and the sun too bright. Not a single cloud could be seen as I took in the scene that looked forced. It was almost as if someone wanted to make this place perfect and went just a bit overboard.
I felt the texture of the grass beneath my toes and I couldn’t pinpoint what about it made my skin crawl. I shivered, turning to the dark figure brooding beside me.
“Where are we?”
He was silent for a while and I tried to occupy my thoughts with the strange scenery rather than the mind-numbing concern of whether or not Mvikeli was ok. A young man ran into the clearing, laughing at something someone just out of sight had said or done. He as tall, with broad shoulders and a lovely laugh that tugged at my memory. Something about him was familiar but try as I might the image of his face could not stay long enough in my mind for me to know what he looked like. He sat under a mango tree and watched as the afternoon passed by in a summer haze. The serenity of the scene eased some of my the tension from my shoulders and neck. I envied him his peace.
“Where are we?”
“Inside a memory”
It was the flat tone of his voice that alerted me to the emotional turmoil raging within him. I reached out for his hand, knowing intuitively that the contact between us was as calming to him as it was to me. He gulped in air as our hands touched as if a man who had been starved of it for a long time. It occurred to me then that I thought of him as a man, and not as this supernatural entity that held an unknown reservoir of power within him.
“My memory.”
I turned back to the man under the tree. Eager to look at his face as he was then. Curious about everything that he was.
“This is the only happy memory I have of my time as human being.”
I pulled him down onto the weird feeling grass and we sat there, side by side as we observed a version of himself bask in the serenity of the afternoon.
“I created this place specifically so that I couldn’t forget my humanity, at the time that I built it, I had been the Angel of Death for too many years to count. I had forgotten so much about who and what I used to be. I don’t really remember what I used to look like. I think that I may have liked mangos. I’m not sure. That’s why when you asked to see my true form I tried to hurt you. I couldn’t remember my form from when I was human, and that was my true form was it not? I was born into being as human, I only became what I am now later. Shouldn’t my human form be my true form?”
It was clearly a rhetorical question, he knew as well as I did that I was out of my depth here. We continued our silent vigil as the human version of himself fell asleep under the tree. The memory was off because he had tried too hard to replicate it. The only thing that felt genuine was the serenity and peace he had felt that day. It was hard to ignore. I thought about the last time I felt that way and it was with Mvikeli standing right next to me, holding on to my hand. The thought of it caused a new wave of pain to crash against my chest. Was he still alive? Would he be okay without me?
I tightened my hold on His hand.
“Do you remember your name?”
A strange strangled sound came from his throat and it took me a while to realise it was a laugh.
“I know every single name they call me now as I am. Most of them are not flattering. But I don’t remember the one my mother gave me. My mother, isn’t that a strange thought? I once had a mother.”
“Can I give you one? I can’t keep referring to you as Him or Death. It’s weird.”
“But that is who I am.”
There was a question that I was burning to ask him. It sat on the tip of my tongue like a red piece of coal. Before I could spit it out, we were jerked from the memory and hurled into darkness. The first thing I noticed was how empty my hand felt. I reached out to him and was met with nothing but empty space. I cried out, feeling the tendrils of panic inching themselves towards my heart. I had never been alone in this realm before. He had always been with me.
“This is not funny. Come back.”
“I’m afraid it’s just the two of us for now.”
The voice was a melody. It couldn’t possibly belong to him. I found myself looking for the owner, ready to lay my soul at their feet for their use. A light appeared in the sky and got brighter until I could feel the sweet caress of the suns rays on my skin. I blinked out the glare of the sun in my eyes only to find that I was still in His memory, only everything was better. The grass felt as grass should feel but better. I felt an intimate connection with every element of nature in a way that I had never felt before. It was as if I was one with the rocks and the blades of grass.
The breeze whispered the coming of a supernatural being. It seemed to me that I blinked and she was in front of me. I remember when I thought that Buhle was beautiful, and yet she paled in comparison to this woman. Her dark chocolate skin seemed to glow from within. The halo of her hair sat on her head like a crown. I had no doubt in my mind of the royalty standing before me. She was life. I saw forests in her eyes, the green of them shocking against the darkness of her skin. She towered over me, standing well over six foot tall.
“Botlhale, it is a pleasure to finally meet you. I am the First, or Mama, I believe the most popular moniker in your era is Mother Nature.”
If I had a body it would have fainted. My mind reeled and all I could manage was a lousy,
“Hi.”
“I am also Death’s wife.”

thread.title: Slutsky's lemma: Alexandroff one-point compactification and Weierstrass theorem
thread.title_full: Slutsky's lemma: Alexandroff one-point compactification and Weierstrass theorem

posts.author: Byung
posts.title: Slutsky's lemma: Alexandroff one-point compactification and Weierstrass theorem
posts.text:
Let $(Y_n)_{n\ge 1}$ and $(Z_n)_{n\ge 1}$ be two sequences of random variables defined on the same space $(\Omega,\mathcal{F},\Bbb{P}).$ 
There is Slutsky's lemma which states: 
$$Y_n\overset{D}\to Y\;\mbox{and}\; Z_n\overset{P}\to c\; \mbox{then}\; (Y_n,Z_n)\overset{D}\to( Y,c).$$ 
which means that foor all $h\in C_b(\Bbb{R}^2),\quad\Bbb{E}h(Y_n,Z_n)\overset{n\to\infty}\to \Bbb{E} h(Y,c).$ 
The proof starts by saying it is sufficient to consider $h$ as $h(y,z)=f(y)g(z).$ 
It doesn't seem trivial at all? I know that for the convergence in distribution it's enough to prove the convergence in a space $\mathcal{H}$ that is total in $C_0(\Bbb{R}).$ 
Perhaps we can use this idea with Weierstrass theorem but we need compact space, perhaps using Alexandroff one-point compactification for $\Bbb{R}^2.$
